WEBVTT

00:06.867 --> 00:11.133
The C-130 Hercules
is past the point of no return,

00:11.167 --> 00:12.867
the point at which
there's not enough fuel

00:12.900 --> 00:14.800
to safely turn back, no matter

00:14.833 --> 00:17.133
what the weather is on the ice.

00:17.167 --> 00:18.733
It's loud back here,

00:18.767 --> 00:22.300
the moan of four massive
props relentless.

00:22.333 --> 00:24.133
I'm dressed like all of us

00:24.167 --> 00:25.393
who've been approved
to make this journey

00:25.400 --> 00:27.167
in the same regulation gear

00:27.200 --> 00:29.367
as required by
the National Science Foundation

00:29.400 --> 00:31.400
for all flights
and means of conveyance

00:31.433 --> 00:34.033
on the ice:
thick goose down parka

00:34.067 --> 00:36.167
known by one and all as Big Red,

00:36.200 --> 00:38.000
heavy waterproof overalls,

00:38.033 --> 00:39.867
inflatable buddy boots,

00:39.900 --> 00:42.100
gloves, long underwear, cap.

00:42.133 --> 00:45.100
I am talking layers.

